<!-- Pokey's Weapon Mod Rebalance - weapon section of equipmentmods.xml only.

     Design (docs/weapon-mod-rebalance-design.md, scorecard in
     docs/weapon-mod-rebalance-v1.md):
     - NO RNG: every roll range is pinned (min = max) - what you craft is
       what you get, rerolling is pointless.
     - BASIC TIER = the seven non-empty COMBINATIONS of the three DPS
       stats (damage, cooling, reload), one mod each, no two sharing an
       effect set. In practice those seven resolve into TWO CLASSES - this
       is STRUCTURAL, not a tuning choice: with only three levers the space
       holds ~four genuinely distinct positions, and the rest are blends
       that overlap what they are built from.
         BASELINE     Piercer (damage). Damage is full value on EVERY
                      weapon, so Piercer is the universal default and the
                      benchmark - not a niche pick.
         SPECIALISTS  Cowboy (reload), Tramontane (cooling), Mistral
                      (cooling+reload). Each PEAKS in one domain and does
                      little outside it: high ceiling, narrow. Mistral is
                      the only pair that earns a real niche, because its
                      two effects SYNERGISE (cooling pays the heat bill so
                      the extra fire rate actually converts to DPS).
         GENERALISTS  Stabber (damage+reload), Gregale (damage+cooling),
                      Slasher (triple). Each blends damage with a stat that
                      is a SUBSTITUTE, not a synergy - so it can never
                      out-damage Piercer nor out-focus a specialist. They
                      live in the tie band as damage-backed SAFE PICKS:
                      never useless, rarely uniquely best. That IS the role
                      (harness signature: high best-or-tied, low strict
                      wins). The current values are a deliberate
                      equilibrium - push a generalist down and Piercer eats
                      its weapons, push it up and it mints a rogue
                      specialist that kills a real one.
       Differentiation budget belongs to Enhanced/Exceptional, spent on
       widening the SPECIALIST peaks so identity sharpens with rarity.
       Effects a mod's combo excludes are pinned to 1.0 in its (data-fixed)
       bonus slots. Tune in the slider tool
       (tools/weapon-mod-rebalance/tuner.html).
     - Secondary bundles stay worth <25% cycle DPS on any weapon (a mod's
       secondaries are part of its combo identity, so this cap sits near
       the strongest single-stat mod's headline, not the old 16%).
     - Structural malus slots that no longer fit a mod's role are pinned
       at exactly 1.0 (no effect); the ware structure is fixed in data, so
       they cannot be removed with attribute replaces.
     - Optional pool entries are pinned too; which pool bonuses appear is
       engine-side selection RNG that game data cannot remove.
     Scenario mods (mod_weapon_damage_fleet_battle_1 - already fixed-value
     in vanilla), the engine/ship/shield sections and weights are
     untouched. -->
<diff>
  <!-- ============================ BASIC (quality 1) ==================== -->

  <!-- Piercer = DAMAGE - the universal BASELINE. Pure damage, full value on
       every weapon, so it is the default pick and the benchmark the others
       are measured against, not a niche mod. Its universality is the
       gravity well the generalists orbit: lower them and Piercer wins their
       weapons outright. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_01_mk1']/@min">1.15</replace><!-- vanilla 1.05 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_01_mk1']/@max">1.15</replace><!-- vanilla 1.2 -->

  <!-- Tramontane = COOLING - SPECIALIST. Pure coolrate: big on the hottest
       heat-limited main guns, nothing on the heatless majority or on
       turrets (which have no heat mechanic - cooling is wasted there). High
       ceiling, narrow. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/cooling[@ware='mod_weapon_cooling_01_mk1']/@min">1.4</replace><!-- vanilla 1.048 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/cooling[@ware='mod_weapon_cooling_01_mk1']/@max">1.4</replace><!-- vanilla 1.216 -->

  <!-- Cowboy = RELOAD - SPECIALIST. Pure fire rate: full value on heatless
       and clip weapons - owns continuous heatless turrets cleanly (no ties)
       - but taxed on heat weapons where faster firing just adds heat. Its
       headline sits above a damage single's because reload is situational
       where damage is universal. Vanilla 0.682-2 crossed 1.0, a lottery. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/reload[@ware='mod_weapon_reload_01_mk1']/@min">1.225</replace><!-- vanilla 0.682 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/reload[@ware='mod_weapon_reload_01_mk1']/@max">1.225</replace><!-- vanilla 2 -->

  <!-- Jumper = CHARGETIME - the charge-weapon SPECIALIST (a small family:
       Ray Ion Projector, Erlking, ...). x0.75 charge time cuts the wind-up
       between shots, plus an +8% damage floor; utility-grade elsewhere.
       Chargetime is outside the three-stat combo matrix - its own axis. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/chargetime[@ware='mod_weapon_chargetime_01_mk1']/@min">0.75</replace><!-- vanilla 0.8 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/chargetime[@ware='mod_weapon_chargetime_01_mk1']/@max">0.75</replace><!-- vanilla 0.95 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/chargetime[@ware='mod_weapon_chargetime_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="1">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>

  <!-- Basic utility mods: primaries pinned at their vanilla best roll
       (max already equals the pin, so only min changes), plus a flat
       +8% damage rider (added forced bonus block - no vanilla
       counterpart) so picking a utility niche costs only ~6% DPS vs the
       Piercer baseline (+15%) instead of all of it - the utility effect
       is meant to be the reason you take it, not a DPS sacrifice.
       Digger (mining) is the one exception - yield is its draw and a
       damage rider on a mining mod re-opens the combat-cheat door.
       Niches:
       Dispatcher = velocity (projectiles arrive faster, range nearly
       unchanged: 1.25 x 0.84 = +5%), Endurance = reach (+21% range
       = 1.1 speed x 1.1 lifetime, flight character unchanged),
       Lens = beam reach (+21%, matching Endurance's range gain),
       Gimbal = turret tracking, Gum = sticky weapons,
       Intruder = anti-surface-element work. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/speed[@ware='mod_weapon_speed_01_mk1']/@min">1.25</replace><!-- vanilla 1.05 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/speed[@ware='mod_weapon_speed_01_mk1']/@max">1.25</replace><!-- vanilla 1.1 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/speed[@ware='mod_weapon_speed_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="2">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
      <lifetime min="0.84" max="0.84"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/beamlength[@ware='mod_weapon_beamlength_01_mk1']/@min">1.21</replace><!-- vanilla 1.05 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/beamlength[@ware='mod_weapon_beamlength_01_mk1']/@max">1.21</replace><!-- vanilla 1.1 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/beamlength[@ware='mod_weapon_beamlength_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="1">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/lifetime[@ware='mod_weapon_lifetime_01_mk1']/@min">1.1</replace><!-- vanilla 1.05 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/lifetime[@ware='mod_weapon_lifetime_01_mk1']/@max">1.1</replace><!-- vanilla 1.2 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/lifetime[@ware='mod_weapon_lifetime_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="2">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
      <speed min="1.1" max="1.1"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/mining[@ware='mod_weapon_mining_01_mk1']/@min">6</replace><!-- vanilla 5.25, max 6 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/rotationspeed[@ware='mod_weapon_rotationspeed_01_mk1']/@min">1.2</replace><!-- vanilla 1.05, max 1.2 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/rotationspeed[@ware='mod_weapon_rotationspeed_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="1">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/sticktime[@ware='mod_weapon_sticktime_01_mk1']/@min">1.2</replace><!-- vanilla 1.05, max 1.2 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/sticktime[@ware='mod_weapon_sticktime_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="1">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/surfaceelement[@ware='mod_weapon_surfaceelement_01_mk1']/@min">1.35</replace><!-- vanilla 1.2, max 1.35 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/surfaceelement[@ware='mod_weapon_surfaceelement_01_mk1']">
    <bonus chance="1.0" max="1">
      <damage min="1.08" max="1.08"/>
    </bonus>
  </add>

  <!-- Stabber = DAMAGE + RELOAD - GENERALIST. Damage backbone with a
       fire-rate lean, aimed at cool-running / clip guns where the reload
       rider converts without a heat penalty. But it can't out-damage
       Piercer (lower damage pin) nor out-rate Cowboy (lower reload than
       1.225), so it lives in the tie band as a damage-backed SAFE PICK -
       high best-or-tied, few strict wins. Push it up and it starts eating
       Cowboy's continuous weapons; push it down and Piercer eats it. The
       native cooling child is pinned to 1.0 (excluded from the combo) and
       a reload child is added; bonus max 1->2 keeps both forced. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_02_mk1']/@min">1.1</replace><!-- vanilla 1.35 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_02_mk1']/@max">1.1</replace><!-- vanilla 1.45 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_02_mk1']/bonus/@max">2</replace><!-- vanilla 1 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_02_mk1']/bonus/cooling/@min">1.0</replace><!-- vanilla 0.684; excluded from combo -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_02_mk1']/bonus/cooling/@max">1.0</replace><!-- vanilla 0.736 -->
  <add sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_02_mk1']/bonus">
    <reload min="1.1" max="1.1"/><!-- new child; no vanilla counterpart -->
  </add>

  <!-- Gregale = DAMAGE + COOLING - GENERALIST. Damage backbone with a
       cooling lean for warm main guns. Same story as Stabber on the other
       axis: can't out-cool Tramontane (1.2 vs 1.4) nor out-damage Piercer,
       so it sits in the tie band as a damage-backed SAFE PICK for heat guns
       - never the sharpest tool, never a wasted slot. Native structure is
       already cooling-primary + a forced damage child (bonus max 1). -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/cooling[@ware='mod_weapon_cooling_02_mk1']/@min">1.2</replace><!-- vanilla 1.38 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/cooling[@ware='mod_weapon_cooling_02_mk1']/@max">1.2</replace><!-- vanilla 1.49 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/cooling[@ware='mod_weapon_cooling_02_mk1']/bonus/damage/@min">1.08</replace><!-- vanilla 0.7 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/cooling[@ware='mod_weapon_cooling_02_mk1']/bonus/damage/@max">1.08</replace><!-- vanilla 0.75 -->

  <!-- Slasher = DAMAGE + COOLING + RELOAD - GENERALIST (the pure
       all-rounder): a bit of everything for weapons that want damage, heat
       headroom, and rate at once. It has the LOWEST peak of any Basic mod -
       spreading the budget across three substitute stats can't beat any
       single-stat or synergy specialist on their home turf - but the
       near-Piercer damage floor keeps it alive in the tie band everywhere.
       The archetypal SAFE PICK: broadest best-or-tied coverage, essentially
       zero strict wins. Native structure is damage-primary + forced cooling
       + reload children (bonus max 2). Cooling/reload stay modest so the
       secondary bundle keeps well under the 25% cap. -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_03_mk1']/@min">1.115</replace><!-- vanilla 1.338 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_03_mk1']/@max">1.115</replace><!-- vanilla 1.503 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_03_mk1']/bonus/cooling/@min">1.07</replace><!-- vanilla 0.681 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_03_mk1']/bonus/cooling/@max">1.07</replace><!-- vanilla 0.74 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_03_mk1']/bonus/reload/@min">1.045</replace><!-- vanilla 0.682 -->
  <replace sel="/equipmentmods/weapon/damage[@ware='mod_weapon_damage_03_mk1']/bonus/reload/@max">1.045</replace><!-- vanilla 2 -->

  <!-- Mistral = COOLING + RELOAD - SPECIALIST (the one pair that earns a
       niche). Cooling and reload SYNERGISE rather than substitute: the extra
       coolrate pays the heat bill that the extra fire rate runs up, so the
       rate actually converts to DPS. That makes it the pick for hot
       rapid-fire guns where Cowboy (rate only) would overheat and Tramontane
       (cooling only) leaves rate on the table - a real peak no single stat
       reaches, unlike the damage-blend generalists. No raw damage at all.
       Native structure is cooling-primary + forced damage + reload children
       (bonus max 2); the damage child is pinned to 1.0 (excluded). -->
